Title: Index Types in PostgreSQL: Learning PostgreSQL with Grant - Simple Talk
Description: As with any other relational data management system (RDBMS), PostgreSQL uses indexes as a mechanism to improve data access. PostgreSQL has a number of different index types, supporting different behaviors and different types of data. In addition, again, similar to other RDBMS, there are properties and behaviors associated with these indexes.  In this article I‚Äôm going to go over the different types of indexes and some index behaviors. We‚Äôll get into what the indexes are, how they work, and how best you can apply them within your databases. I‚Äôm hoping you‚Äôll develop an understanding of which indexes are likely to work better in each situation.
